n\">(<span class=\"fn\">f'_surj</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Function.html#Function.Surjective\">Function.Surjective</a> <span class=\"fn\">f'</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">g</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">X</span> → <span class=\"fn\">S</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hg</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#Continuous\">Continuous</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">g'</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Y</span> → <span class=\"fn\">T</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hg'</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#Continuous\">Continuous</a> <span class=\"fn\">g'</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h_comm</span> : <span class=\"fn\">g'</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Function.comp\">∘</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">f'</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Function.comp\">∘</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Y</span> → <span class=\"fn\">S</span></span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#Continuous\">Continuous</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">f'</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Function.comp\">∘</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">g'</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Function.comp\">∘</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"This is the key statement for the inductive proof of injectivity of light profinite spaces.\nGiven a commutative square\n```\nX >-f->  Y\n|g       |g'\nv        v\nS -f'->> T\n```\nwhere `Y` is profinite, `S` is finite, `f` is injective and `f'` is surjective,\nthere exists a diagonal map `k : Y → S` making the diagram commute.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Category/LightProfinite/Injective.html#Profinite.exists_lift_of_finite_of_injective_of_surjective","kind":"theorem","line":48,"name":"Profinite.exists_lift_of_finite_of_injective_of_surjective","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Topology/Category/LightProfinite/Injective.lean#L48-L116"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Preadditive.Injective.Basic","Mathlib.Topology.Category.LightProfinite.AsLimit","Mathlib.Topology.Category.CompHausLike.Limits","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Functor.OfSequence","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.EpiMono","Mathlib.Order.RelClasses"],"instances":[{"className":"CategoryTheory.Injective","name":"Profinite.injective_of_finite","typeNames":[]},{"className":"CategoryTheory.Injective","name":"Profinite.injective_of_light","typeNames":["CategoryTheory.Functor.obj"]},{"className":"CategoryTheory.Injective","name":"LightProfinite.injective","typeNames":[]}],"name":"Mathlib.Topology.Category.LightProfinite.Injective"}